author: lemifn
description: In response to declining birth rates and shrinking student populations, some rural schools in South Korea have enrolled elderly women-particularly grandmothers who never had the opportunity to learn to read or write-to keep their classrooms open. For example, Bangrim Primary School in Gangwon Province, which once had nearly 700 students, saw its enrollment drop to just 22. To prevent closure, the school began admitting elderly women like 72-year-old Park Go-ee, who now attends classes alongside much younger students to learn the literacy skills she missed earlier in life. This initiative not only helps sustain rural schools but also offers lifelong learning opportunities for seniors, enhancing their social inclusion and mental well-being. Studies have shown that literacy education for rural seniors in South Korea is positively linked to greater social inclusion and improved mental health. As South Korea continues to grapple with one of the world's lowest fertility rates, such innovative approaches serve a dual purpose: preserving educational institutions in rural areas and empowering elderly citizens through education. #fyp #blowup #story #school

author: _cointel
description: We Made The Zoot Suit of the Decade. For the past few months, we‚Äôve been building something special. Spike Lee wanted to channel ‚ÄúShorty‚Äù, his iconic character from Malcolm X and reintroduce him to the world, this time with the wisdom, vision, and fire of 2025. We took that challenge personally. What followed was a journey through sketches, fittings, setbacks, breakthroughs, and above all craftsmanship. Every inch of this suit was drafted from scratch. We custom dyed grosgrain for each stripe, hand-cut every panel, sourced gold buttons to echo Harlem Renaissance elegance, and built the silhouette from a muslin draft to final fitting. It wasn‚Äôt just a suit. It was a resurrection. A cultural blueprint. A modern revival of the unapologetic flair of 1940s zoot suits, reimagined through a contemporary Black lens. And we believe, we made the zoot suit of the decade. This was made with no factory. Just vision, grit, and trust. Design and creative direction by COINTEL. Thank you, Spike, for trusting us to dress the moment. This is only the beginning. #COINTEL #ZootSuitOfTheDecade #SpikeLee #Cannes2025

author: nypost
description: The New Jersey train conductor just busted for allegedly horribly abusing a girl for years had been hailed for job heroics in February, it emerged ‚Äî along with new details about her escape. Branndon Mosley, 41, was heralded for his actions during a Feb. 6 SEPTA train fire ‚Äî weeks before he and his girlfriend were charged May 11 with confining and abusing the girl, who was 11 when the torture started and is now 18, according to a report. The child was forced to live in a dog crate for a year and at one point had only a bucket for a toilet in the couple‚Äôs ‚Äúsqualid‚Äù animal-filled home, Camden County prosecutors said. The girl‚Äôs relationship to the pair was not immediately known. Mosley and gal pal Brenda Spencer, 38, both of Gloucester Township are accused of physically and mentally abusing the girl before she finally escaped to the house of a neighbor who helped get her to safety. Mosley also is accused of sexually abusing the child. ‚ÄúShe told me just recently that they cut her hair and shaved her head for punishment,‚Äù the neighbor who helped rescue the child told Fox 29. ‚ÄúShe said they kept her in the dog crate. It was horrific, it was disgraceful,‚Äù said the resident, who only wanted to go by Susan. ‚ÄúWe were both in tears, me and my son. We couldn‚Äôt believe it.‚Äù The sickening allegations surfaced just weeks after Mosley jumped into action when a train traveling from west Trenton, NJ, to Newark, Del., caught on fire near the Crum Lynne Station in Pennsylvania in February, Fox 29 reported. All 325 passengers and four crew members on board evacuated safely, officials said. Mosley was honored by SEPTA for his actions in the incident, with Fox 29 obtaining a photo of the emotionless conductor holding up a framed certificate. SEPTA did not immediately return an email or call seeking comment. The alleged abuser has been with the transit agency for 18 years and has since been taken off duty, a SEPTA spokesperson told the station. Mosley and Spencer were charged with first-degree kidnapping, second-degree aggravated assault, aggravated assault with a deadly weapon and a slew of other criminal counts. Mosley is also separately facing charges of first-degree aggravated sexual assault and second-degree sexual assault, prosecutors said. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know what to think because you know the people next door. You talk to them, you never know what‚Äôs happening in there,‚Äù the neighbor, Susan, told the station. ‚ÄúIt is so unreal to me to know what was happening right next door to me.‚Äù üì∏: SEPTA; Camden County Prosecutor's Office
